\section{Constructing Universal Constants}

\subsection{Algorithmic Construction Process}

The construction of binary representations for physical constants follows a systematic algorithmic process:

\begin{algorithm}
\caption{Binary Representation Construction Algorithm}
\label{alg:construction}
\begin{algorithmic}[1]
\Procedure{ConstructBinaryRepresentation}{$g_{target}$, $\epsilon$}
\State Initialize $g_{current} \gets 0$
\State Initialize empty binary sequence $B$
\State Determine polar measure $\hat{\tau}$ for $g_{target}$
\For{each position $n$ in sequence}
    \If{$n$ is odd}
        \If{$g_{current} + 2^{(|\hat{\tau}| - n)/2} \leq g_{target}$}
            \State Set $c_{\rho_n} \gets 1$
            \State $g_{current} \gets g_{current} + 2^{(|\hat{\tau}| - n)/2}$
        \Else
            \State Set $c_{\rho_n} \gets 0$
        \EndIf
    \ElsIf{$n$ is even}
        \If{$g_{current} + 2^{-(n - |\hat{\tau}|)/2} \leq g_{target}$}
            \State Set $c_{e_{\rho_n}} \gets 1$
            \State $g_{current} \gets g_{current} + 2^{-(n - |\hat{\tau}|)/2}$
        \Else
            \State Set $c_{e_{\rho_n}} \gets 0$
        \EndIf
    \EndIf
    \If{$|g_{current} - g_{target}| < \epsilon$}
        \State \textbf{break}
    \EndIf
\EndFor
\State \Return Binary sequence $B$ and polar measure $\hat{\tau}$
\EndProcedure
\end{algorithmic}
\end{algorithm}

This algorithm iteratively constructs the binary representation by determining whether to include each power of 2 (for integers) or 1/2 (for fractions) to best approximate the target value within the specified precision $\epsilon$.

